	<li>You can send mail to the following postal address: <%= raw address_summary(@vc_address, false, false)%></li>
</ol>
<p>Additionally, upon receipt of any communication from The Visible Closet, to unsubscribe from future communications, you can click on the link that says “If you do not wish to receive these emails in the future, You can click here to unsubscribe.”</p>

<p>Because The Visible Closet provides its California users with the ability to exercise his or her “opt out” rights as described above, pursuant to Section 1798.83 (c)(2) of the California Civil Code, The Visible Closet is in compliance with the California “Shine the Light” law and is not obligated to provide California users with the names and addresses of all the third parties that received personal information from The Visible Closet for the third parties’ direct marketing purposes during the preceding calendar year.</p> 

<p>Please be aware that third party websites accessible through thevisiblecloset.com may collect personally identifiable information about you. The information practices of those third party websites are governed by their own privacy policies and are not covered by this privacy statement, and The Vislble Closet is not responsible for any information that you provide when you access those websites.</p>
