<div class="simple_header">What information does The Visible Closet collect?</div>
<div class="simple_body">
<p>Some functions require users to register before they can use or access a particular area of thevisiblecloset.com (which may be necessary for identification, security, or marketing purposes, etc.).  USERS UNDER THE AGE OF 13 ARE PROHIBITED FROM REGISTERING ON THEVISIBLECLOSET.COM.  The Visible Closet’s registration, online surveys, contest entry forms, and specialized services may call for users to provide personally identifiable information and demographic information (like their age or income level).  Additionally, the registration process requires users to choose a user ID and password.  Users may change his or her password, as well as any personally identifiable information provided to us to keep his or her registration information current. </p>

<p>We use the standard “cookie” feature of major browser applications to allow us to store data about your visit (such data is stored in the aggregate form). Cookies help us learn which areas of thevisiblecloset.com are useful and which areas need improvement. We may use cookies in a number of ways, including keeping track of user return visits to thevisiblecloset.com or our advertisers’ or business partners’ websites; accumulating and reporting aggregate, statistical information in connection with user visits; and to deliver to our users content specific to their interests; to save users ID, passwords, or other information so users don’t have to re-enter it each time they visit our site.  We also may use cookies to track visits to track your progress and number of entries in some of our promotions, sweepstakes, and contests. </p>

<p>Links to other websites may also contain cookies. These third party companies may employ cookies and other technologies to measure advertising effectiveness. You should be aware that different rules may apply to the collection, or use of the personally identifiable information you disclose to these third parties. </p>

<p>thevisiblecloset.com may also gather anonymous information, which may be used by us or shared with third parties. This is information which does not personally identify you, but which may be helpful for marketing purposes or for improving the services we offer. Generally this information is collected through “traffic data” and may entail the use of numeric codes used to identify a computer.</p>
</div>

<div class="simple_header">What does The Visible Closet do with collected information?</div>
<div class="simple_body">
<p>The Visible Closet’s primary goal in collecting personal information is to provide the user with a customized experience on our site. This includes personalization services, interactive communications, and many other types of services. By knowing a little about users, The Visible Closet is able to deliver better service to our users.</p>

<p>We use personally identifiable information from our online registration, surveys, contests, specialized services, and order forms for our own internal evaluation and tracking purposes and to send our users information from our company (e.g., site announcements, newsletters, and message notifications) and promotional material from some of our business partners (or from other companies). If you supply such personally identifiable information, it may also be used to contact you about products and services in which you have indicated an interest, and may be shared with our third party business partners or other companies who may want to contact you, if you have provided your consent through an “opt in” (in which case their use of your personally identifiable information is subject to such third party’s privacy policy). Additionally, you may opt out of receiving future mailings by using the “opt out” procedures described below – see the Choice/Opt-Out section below.</p>

<p>The Visible Closet may use users’ IP address (the number assigned to your computer while it is on the Internet) for our internal purposes to help diagnose problems with our server, and to administer our site. In addition, your IP address is transmitted with each message sent from your account.  We may also store communicative information including, without limitation, instant messages and submissions to personal profiles or social networking communications tools for the purpose of delivering and, if needed, monitoring communications.</p>

<p>Demographic and profile data from online forms or cookies may be used to identify your preferences and this information may be shared with our business partners or other companies only on an aggregate basis, unless you expressly state through an opt-out that demographic and profile information about you may not be disclosed.</p>
</div>

