<div class="simple_body">
<p>The Site may disclose user’s personally identifiable information to third parties (i) when we have his or her consent (through an "opt in"), in which case their use of a user’s information is subject to such third party’s own privacy policy; (ii) when users use co-branded services on the Site and provide any personally identifiable information to any of our third party co-branded business partners (where users are consenting to provide this information to such co-branding partner). Additionally, such third party’s use of a user’s information is subject to such third party’s own privacy policy; (iii) when we have retained companies to work with or on behalf of the Site to provide products, goods or services; (iv) if required to do so by law or in the good faith belief that such action is necessary to comply with a legal process served on the Site, or the Foundation or their respective parent companies, subsidiaries or affiliate, by a governmental agency, court or other entity (e.g., to respond to subpoenas, court orders or other legal process); (v) if we believe a user’s actions violate any law, regulation, our Terms of Use or any of our guidelines for promotions, product offerings or any other features of thevisiblecloset.com, or if a user threatens the rights, property or safety of thevisiblecloset.com, other users, or any other party; (vi) as and when we, in our sole discretion, and in the good-faith belief believe that such disclosure is necessary or appropriate to investigate or resolve possible problems or inquiries, to protect our business and assets, to defend our interests, rights or property of The Visible Closet, and/or to comply with our legal and regulatory obligations; or (vii) in the event of a bankruptcy, or a merger, acquisition, joint venture or other business combination involving The Visible Closet.  Also, personally identifiable information you provide to The Visible Closet may be stored outside of the country in which you reside.</p>
</div>
